headline: From Silicon To Steel: The Value Trade Returns
summary: US markets diverged as soft labor data fueled a 4% small-cap rally while Nasdaq fell 2% on AI doubts and mixed REIT earnings trends. Check out why value wins.

headline: Is Digital Realty (DLR) Pricing Look Attractive After Recent Multi Year Share Gains
summary: If you are wondering whether Digital Realty Trust is priced attractively right now, it helps to start by lining up its recent share performance against what you are getting for that price. The stock last closed at US$171.62, with returns of 3.4% over the past week, 8.2% over the last 30 days, 10.7% year to date, 5.3% over 1 year, 70.7% over 3 years and 45.7% over 5 years.
